==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guaiacum
<hw>Gua"ia*cum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Sp.
<ets>guayaco</ets>, from native name in Haiti.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of small, crooked trees, growing in
tropical America.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The heart wood or the resin of the <spn>Guaiacum
officinale</spn> or lignum-vit⟦ae⟧, a large tree of the West Indies and
Central America. It is much used in medicine.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>guaiac</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guaira</ent>⟦br⟧
